cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.GR 

The paper deals with deep learning for image processing, specifically spectral reconstruction from RGB images. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a moderately deep CNN model, which suggests that it may fall under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the use of deep learning models for image processing can also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with image super-resolution, which falls under the category of cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the benchmarks used in the paper are related to graphics and visualization, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of cs.GR (Graphics).
